llmDefinedChunks.text: [NAV_START] About Us Our Services Resources Book appointment Contact Us Dashboard Signup Login [NAV_END] EN # How to start a business in Australia Discover the essential steps and optimal timing to kickstart your entrepreneurial journey. Get Started Starting a business can be approached in various ways. While not every step may be suitable for everyone, it is advised by us to carefully consider and evaluate these recommendations. ## Steps to starting a business 1. Market Research 2. Business Plan 3. Business Budgeting and Forecasting 4. Pricing strategies and Cost of Goods Sold 5. Business Structure 6. Small Business Accounting 7. Registering a Business 8. Your Obligations #### 1. Market Research Market research is vital when starting a business because it gives you important information about the industry, what customers want, and who your competitors are. This helps you make smart decisions and increases your chances of long-term success. Learn more #### 2. Creating a Solid Business Plan Writing abusiness plan is like crafting a roadmap for your business idea, helping youunderstand it better and providing a guide for making it happen. Learn more #### 3. Managing Finances for a Small Businesses It's time to crunch some numbers for your business

idea. Budgeting and forecasting play a key role in this process. Learn more #### 4. Pricing Strategies and Cost of Goods Sold The pricing strategy you adopt has a direct impact on both your sales volume and the profitability of each transaction. Learn more #### 5. Business Structure The structure of your business determines key aspects, including administrative responsibilities, tax implications, and legal status. Learn more #### 6. Small Business Accounting The structure of your business determines key aspects, including administrative responsibilities, tax implications, and legal status. Learn more #### 7. Registering a Business Following the excitement of choosing to start a business, there are essential paperwork tasks ahead, including ABN application, registration with ASIC, and more. Learn more #### 8. Your obligations As a business in Australia, you are subject to various obligations at the local, state, and federal levels. These obligations cover a range of areas to ensure legal compliance, fair practices, and public safety. Learn more Y&S Accounting proudly specialises in providing professional consulting and accounting services to the Latin American community in Australia since 2008.
